And α is the probability of a type I error and β is the probability of a type II error. For a fair comparison, we usually fix α and compare β. A small β is considered better. The average run length (ARL) is the number of points that, on average will be plotted on a control chart before an OC signal. If a manufacturing or business process is IC:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
